# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — AI Crypto Trading Bot
#
# Build context: project root (used by both infra/Dockerfile.api and
# infra/Dockerfile.ui with `docker build -f infra/Dockerfile.* .`)
#
# Principle: exclude everything that is NOT explicitly copied by a Dockerfile
# stage. Both Dockerfiles use selective COPY directives, so this file's job
# is defence-in-depth: prevent large or sensitive directories from ever being
# transferred to the Docker daemon, which directly impacts build speed and
# image security.
#
# What IS needed in the build context (do NOT exclude):
#   Dockerfile.api:  apps/api/pyproject.toml  apps/api/uv.lock
#                    packages/
#                    apps/api/  (app source in runtime stage)
#   Dockerfile.ui:   apps/ui/package.json  apps/ui/package-lock.json
#                    apps/ui/pnpm-lock.yaml  apps/ui/yarn.lock
#                    apps/ui/  (full UI source in builder stage)
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Version control
# Never send VCS metadata into the build context — adds hundreds of MB on
# large repos and leaks commit history and potentially sensitive config.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python artifacts
# __pycache__ and compiled bytecode are CPU-arch and Python-version specific;
# they would be stale or incorrect inside the container image.
# Build venvs and caches are re-created inside the Dockerfile by uv.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.pyo
**/*.pyd
**/*.so
**/*.egg
**/*.egg-info
**/*.dist-info
**/.eggs

# Python virtual environments
.venv
venv
env
ENV
.env.local
.virtualenv

# Python tool caches
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
.dmypy.json
dmypy.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test coverage artifacts
# Coverage data and HTML reports are large and irrelevant at build time.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.coverage
.coverage.*
coverage.xml
coverage.json
htmlcov

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Node / Next.js artifacts
# node_modules are installed fresh inside the deps stage; shipping them in
# context would be wasteful (can exceed 500 MB) and may contain wrong-arch
# binaries.  .next and out are intermediate/output build directories.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/node_modules
apps/ui/.next
apps/ui/out

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IDE and editor files
# Project-level IDE configs have no function inside a container.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.orig
*~

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS-generated files
# macOS Finder, Windows Explorer, and Linux desktop metadata files.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project documentation and planning artifacts
# Heavy markdown, diagrams, and planning docs are never referenced by any
# COPY directive in either Dockerfile.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
docs/
Documentation/
reports/
*.md
# Exception: README.md is conventionally useful in the image for inspection
!README.md

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Claude agent configuration and workflows
# Internal tooling that has no role in the production container.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/
memory/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub / CI configuration
# GitHub Actions workflows, issue templates, and PR config are not needed
# inside a container image.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.github/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test suites
# Tests are executed in CI, not inside the production image.
# The conftest.py at project root is also excluded.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
tests/
conftest.py

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment / secret files
# Only .env.example (no real secrets) is safe to include.
# Actual .env files must NEVER enter the build context.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Log files and directories
# Runtime logs belong on mounted volumes or a log aggregator, not in the image.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.log.*
logs/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ML model artifacts
# Large binary blobs — models are loaded at runtime from object storage or a
# mounted volume, not baked into the image.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
models/
model_artifacts/
*.pkl
*.joblib
*.onnx
*.pt
*.pth
*.h5

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Miscellaneous build and CI artifacts
# Temporary files, local overrides, and infra-as-code state files.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.tmp
*.temp
dist/
build/
.build/
